  Hard to imagine that a change from a slower machine to a faster one
  can have its disadvantages, too. You may find out for example, that
  certain graphic programs and games will suddenly stampede your
  screen and give you rather a vicious headache than visual pleasure.
  Run included oldtimer DAZZLER.COM on a fast machine to experience
  what I mean.

  Ironically enough, you may have a whole bunch of utilities to speed
  up the screen display, while you are desperately looking for one to
  calibrate speed down. So it goes...

  Then you remember vaguely, there has been around some utility for
  that purpose... Now you have ONLY to come up with the programs name:
  Was it Slow..? Calm..? Quiet..? No, much more common:




