  If you have fast graphic programs, applications or demos without
  inbuild options or switches to regulate their speed, the TSR WHOA!
  can slow down them in most cases (see WHOA!.DOC). I'll add here some
  undocumented features:

  When WHOA! goes resident it will take about 20 Kb of RAM. Loading
  WHOA! successively twice the program comes up with the message
  "Uninstalled". Unfortunately this is not true, as every memory
  mapper will show. That's why I added MARK.COM and RELEASE.EXE to
  this package. Use these utilities in connection with WHOA! (and
  SLOWA) to free up memory consumed by these programs.

  Included DAZ12.BAT demonstrates, how DAZZLER.COM should be run with
  MARK and RELEASE, thus uninstalling WHOA! from memory after exit.

  The calibration speed for WHOA! is normally set via hotkey ALT-F10.
  However, settings straight from the command line are also possible
  (specially useful for batch files). Like this:

  WHOA! -435 ÕÕº  [slowest value]

